News24 CorrespondentRhino horn recovered in the KZN arrests. (Supplied: SAPS) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban &ndash; Two people have been arrested in KwaZulu-Natal after being found in possession of a rhino horn, as well as pieces from a hunting rifle and ammunition, police said on Monday."Members of a national project team set up to combat the poaching of rhinos in the country arrested&hellip;a man and a woman," said Brigadier Vishnu Naidoo in a statement.He said that officials had been "working around the clock" following up on information received, when on Sunday midday they spotted a Mercedes Benz which they had been investigating, in Ntambanana in KwaZulu-Natal."The driver, a 44-year-old woman, and a 33-year-old male, from Hazyview, Mpumalanga, were arrested after the team found a rhino horn and parts of a hunting rifle and ammunition in the vehicle."The two are expected to appear in the Ngwelezana Magistrate&rsquo;s Court on Monday."They are likely to face charges of unlawful possession of a rhino horn and unlawful possession of ammunition."Further charges may be added, said Naidoo.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.